                Manliae Psy<lb break="no" n="2"/>chi <note>sic</note> Manli<supplied reason="lost">us</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Carp<supplied reason="lost">o</supplied>pho<lb break="no" n="4"/>rus et Ma<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">r</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/>ce filia<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied> po<lb break="no" n="6"/>suerunt <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Aemili<lb break="no" n="8"/>us <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertus</ex></expan> ami<supplied reason="lost">cae</supplied> <lb n="9"/>optim<supplied reason="lost">ae</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(A): Abweichung in Maßen. (BC): Manlia [L(uci) f(ilia)?] Ps[y]/che Manli[us] / Carpopho/rus et Mys[i]/ce filia po/suerunt se[p]ul(turam) Aemili / Iusti ami[ci] / optim[i]. - Z. 1/2: Ps[y]/chi - González. Maße Inschriftenfeld beziehen sich auf beschriftete Fläche. J. González u. J. Alvar denken an Ehreninschrift, Postament. Ende 3.-Anfang 4. Jh. - González.</p>
            </div>
